  "notes": "Direct access to iranopendata.org confirmed blocked: GET https://iranopendata.org/en/ (homepage) returns HTTP 200 with real content even with Accept-Language header added, but GET https://iranopendata.org/en/dataset and https://iranopendata.org/api/3/action/package_list both return HTTP 403 with a genuine Cloudflare 'Just a moment...' JS-challenge page (verified via body signature: title 'Just a moment...', 'Enable JavaScript and cookies', challenges.cloudflare.com CSP directive) -- confirms this is a real bot-challenge, not a lightweight block, and curl cannot pass it. Retried with extra headers (Accept-Language, Referer) per task instructions; still blocked, so did not retry further (2 attempts as instructed) and fell back to Wayback Machine. IOD is a CKAN 2.9.2 instance; dataset landing pages under /en/dataset/<slug> ARE archived by Wayback and reachable via web.archive.org/web/{ts}id_/. Each dataset page links to its actual CSV file hosted on a SEPARATE domain, media.iranopendata.org, which does not resolve directly from this network (DNS failure, curl exit 6) but IS independently and extensively archived by Wayback (found ~470 archived media.iranopendata.org files via a broad CDX domain query). Searched that CDX list for economically-relevant filenames (gdp/inflation/cpi/trade/export/import/budget/employment/unemployment/gas/oil/exchange-rate keywords) and found ~80 candidate files; downloaded 17 of the most data-rich and clearly macro/sectoral ones, spanning CPI/inflation by expenditure decile, balance of payments, non-oil trade, USD/rial exchange rate (2011-2020 daily series), unemployment/employment by province, natural gas consumption, crude oil & gold prices, milk powder trade, greenhouse gas emissions, and stock exchange activity. Two files were deliberately EXCLUDED after initial download: cbibf2017 (recipients of government currency at preferential rates, 1397-1399) and cbibf209 (recipients of 4200-toman FX rate for imports, 1398) turned out on inspection to be individual-level lists of named private persons with national ID numbers (~146k and ~150k rows) -- personal transparency/anti-corruption data, not aggregate economic statistics, and out of scope for this database; they were downloaded, inspected, and deleted rather than kept. Column headers in the retained files are in Persian (original); English descriptions are provided in this manifest's table_title fields per SOURCES.md convention of keeping original filenames/headers and adding English titles.",
